channel.title: Cannot move a corrupted file
channel.description:
I just disregarded it, since it's not really any use anymore.... [i]buuuut[/i]
I had a character file created in my folder and it wasn't "completed". And whenever I'd try to delete it, or move to folder containing it, or do anything with it at that matter, it would say "file corrupted, can not be edited" or something like that. The thing is invincible, and i can't get rid of it... lol, i just took everything out of the source folder except that and moved it... I just ignore it now. Anyone have this problem before?
Just curious, doesn't really bother me.
